1
00:00:20,180 --> 00:00:26,020
=Manbo Destiny=

2
00:00:26,020 --> 00:00:27,980
=Episode 23=

3
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:34,930
The medicine.

4
00:00:36,015 --> 00:00:36,785
Imperial Concubine.

5
00:00:37,660 --> 00:00:38,470
Give me the medicine.

6
00:00:44,062 --> 00:00:45,062
Give me the medicine.

7
00:00:45,760 --> 00:00:46,601
Give me the medicine.

8
00:00:55,100 --> 00:00:55,984
Saul.

9
00:00:57,369 --> 00:00:58,484
Saul.

10
00:00:59,446 --> 00:01:02,715
This is the critical moment
to overthrow the Reformists.

11
00:01:04,100 --> 00:01:05,984
If she dies,

12
00:01:06,715 --> 00:01:08,715
the Reformists will be leaderless,

13
00:01:09,215 --> 00:01:11,061
and the reform will fail completely.

14
00:01:11,984 --> 00:01:12,330
You...

15
00:01:12,638 --> 00:01:13,753
You want me to kill someone?

16
00:01:21,523 --> 00:01:22,600
We are merely

17
00:01:23,446 --> 00:01:25,407
seizing every opportunity.

18
00:01:29,369 --> 00:01:30,484
To win without a fight.

19
00:01:40,127 --> 00:01:40,935
Imperial Concubine.

20
00:01:42,060 --> 00:01:42,935
Give me the medicine.

21
00:01:58,280 --> 00:01:59,433
You are the mastermind

22
00:01:59,700 --> 00:02:00,920
behind the late queen's death.

23
00:02:01,318 --> 00:02:02,549
At most, I was an accomplice.

24
00:02:03,203 --> 00:02:04,549
If you don't help me,

25
00:02:04,549 --> 00:02:05,395
at worst,

26
00:02:05,818 --> 00:02:07,703
we perish together.

27
00:02:12,972 --> 00:02:14,433
How do you expect me to help you?

28
00:02:15,549 --> 00:02:16,549
Make Song Pai

29
00:02:17,203 --> 00:02:19,087
never able to rise again.

30
00:02:25,049 --> 00:02:26,203
Understood.

31
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:37,608
Na.

32
00:02:39,531 --> 00:02:40,223
Na.

33
00:02:41,915 --> 00:02:44,300
You are truly beyond redemption.

34
00:02:45,569 --> 00:02:46,185
Dad.

35
00:02:46,723 --> 00:02:48,377
You can't imprison me here.

36
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:49,992
I have the right to help my friends.

37
00:02:49,992 --> 00:02:50,531
Enough.

38
00:02:51,685 --> 00:02:52,531
I'm telling you,

39
00:02:53,454 --> 00:02:55,108
without my permission,

40
00:02:55,415 --> 00:02:57,185
you are not stepping outside this house.

41
00:02:58,339 --> 00:02:58,877
Dad.

42
00:03:01,069 --> 00:03:03,262
I married into the Manbo royal family.

43
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:05,723
I am now the Second Princess of Manbo.

44
00:03:11,685 --> 00:03:13,877
Honorable Second Princess.

45
00:03:15,886 --> 00:03:18,848
You are nothing more
than my hostage now.

46
00:03:20,386 --> 00:03:21,579
Stay where you are.

47
00:03:21,963 --> 00:03:25,463
Don't even think
about doing anything against the family.

48
00:03:27,271 --> 00:03:27,771
Dad.

49
00:03:29,655 --> 00:03:30,117
Dad.

50
00:03:30,771 --> 00:03:31,271
Dad!

51
00:03:32,271 --> 00:03:33,155
Guard her strictly.

52
00:03:33,848 --> 00:03:34,579
Dad!

53
00:03:34,655 --> 00:03:35,502
Open the door!

54
00:03:37,002 --> 00:03:38,271
Let me out!

55
00:03:38,771 --> 00:03:39,309
Dad!

56
00:03:45,160 --> 00:03:46,429
I want this handled immediately.

57
00:03:46,776 --> 00:03:47,699
Do you hear me?

58
00:03:51,814 --> 00:03:52,622
Pai.

59
00:03:53,583 --> 00:03:54,314
Something's wrong.

60
00:03:55,352 --> 00:03:56,699
Na has been imprisoned by Saul.

61
00:03:56,700 --> 00:03:57,790
He won't let her see anyone.

62
00:03:57,968 --> 00:03:58,929
How could this happen?

63
00:03:59,952 --> 00:04:01,299
To go against me,

64
00:04:02,414 --> 00:04:04,145
Saul even imprisoned his own daughter.

65
00:04:04,568 --> 00:04:06,106
Pai, you know something, don't you?

66
00:04:07,222 --> 00:04:08,452
Saul was the one who leaked

67
00:04:08,452 --> 00:04:10,183
the contract marriage scandal.

68
00:04:10,414 --> 00:04:12,068
Wen Shanna definitely wanted to help us.

69
00:04:12,452 --> 00:04:14,376
But I think Saul has her under control.

70
00:04:14,683 --> 00:04:15,606
That jerk.

71
00:04:16,068 --> 00:04:17,068
Lin Ge, calm down.

72
00:04:18,106 --> 00:04:18,722
Lin Ge.

73
00:04:19,299 --> 00:04:19,952
I think

74
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:22,491
if we draw public attention,

75
00:04:23,068 --> 00:04:24,837
we might force Saul to release her.

76
00:04:26,376 --> 00:04:27,222
Use the media.

77
00:04:27,799 --> 00:04:29,029
Expose every conspiracy.

78
00:04:29,337 --> 00:04:32,145
That will pressure Saul
to change his mind.

79
00:04:34,529 --> 00:04:36,491
All the forces behind Saul

80
00:04:37,337 --> 00:04:38,645
must be completely uprooted.

81
00:04:42,260 --> 00:04:43,145
Next question.

82
00:04:43,760 --> 00:04:45,029
Your Highness,

83
00:04:45,414 --> 00:04:46,991
why did you choose a contract marriage?

84
00:04:50,145 --> 00:04:51,606
Our contract

85
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:53,914
was originally meant
to stabilize the royal situation.

86
00:04:54,529 --> 00:04:55,222
At the beginning,

87
00:04:55,414 --> 00:04:57,568
we were both under
immense external pressure.

88
00:04:58,722 --> 00:05:01,068
So this arrangement
benefited both sides.

89
00:05:01,337 --> 00:05:03,260
Isn't that deceiving the public?

90
00:05:03,491 --> 00:05:05,068
But as time went on,

91
00:05:05,645 --> 00:05:07,222
Song Pai and I,

92
00:05:07,568 --> 00:05:09,220
developed genuine feelings
for each other.

93
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:20,754
We know the public has many questions.

94
00:05:21,870 --> 00:05:23,062
Some people support us.

95
00:05:24,254 --> 00:05:25,562
Some criticize us.

96
00:05:27,370 --> 00:05:29,293
But what I want to say is,

97
00:05:30,370 --> 00:05:32,177
the feelings between Mengmeng and me

98
00:05:32,408 --> 00:05:33,793
have stood the test.

99
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:37,293
And we both

100
00:05:38,139 --> 00:05:39,408
chose each other.

101
00:05:47,908 --> 00:05:48,600
Mengmeng.

102
00:05:49,985 --> 00:05:52,023
No matter how the world
criticizes us today,

103
00:05:52,908 --> 00:05:53,716
remember this,

104
00:05:55,139 --> 00:05:56,600
I will always stand by you,

105
00:05:57,677 --> 00:05:58,754
and protect you.

106
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:02,370
Our contract is just the beginning.

107
00:06:04,062 --> 00:06:05,831
But it will never be the end.

108
00:06:08,639 --> 00:06:10,370
Support Song Pai and Guan Mengmeng!

109
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:36,635
You take this route.

110
00:06:36,943 --> 00:06:37,712
You and him,

111
00:06:37,943 --> 00:06:38,904
enter from here.

112
00:06:40,366 --> 00:06:40,981
Right here.

113
00:06:41,250 --> 00:06:41,904
Surround him.

114
00:06:42,300 --> 00:06:43,481
You provide support from here.

115
00:06:44,135 --> 00:06:45,173
Use force if necessary.

116
00:06:45,173 --> 00:06:45,866
Understood?

117
00:06:46,443 --> 00:06:47,135
Understood.

118
00:07:01,558 --> 00:07:03,943
- Mr. Saul
- Mr. Saul

119
00:07:03,943 --> 00:07:05,981
Why did you reveal the First Prince's
contract marriage?

120
00:07:05,981 --> 00:07:07,020
Please give a truthful explanation.

121
00:07:07,020 --> 00:07:08,750
It's all false news, rumors.

122
00:07:08,750 --> 00:07:10,212
No need to respond.

123
00:07:11,981 --> 00:07:13,443
So you want to use royal scandals

124
00:07:13,443 --> 00:07:14,597
to gain more power?

125
00:07:15,520 --> 00:07:16,443
I have always

126
00:07:16,712 --> 00:07:18,866
worked for the stability and prosperity

127
00:07:19,250 --> 00:07:20,481
of this country diligently.

128
00:07:21,960 --> 00:07:23,673
Are you engaging
in political manipulation?

129
00:07:23,673 --> 00:07:25,597
How do you explain imprisoning
the Second Princess?

130
00:07:25,597 --> 00:07:26,366
Imprisoning?

131
00:07:26,866 --> 00:07:27,943
What a joke.

132
00:07:28,250 --> 00:07:29,443
She is my own daughter.

133
00:07:29,635 --> 00:07:30,827
I am her father.

134
00:07:31,250 --> 00:07:33,173
How could I imprison my own daughter?

135
00:07:33,712 --> 00:07:34,481
As we know,

136
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:36,866
Song Pai and Guan Mengmeng
have already gathered evidence.

137
00:07:37,212 --> 00:07:39,135
Are you afraid it will be made public?

138
00:07:39,712 --> 00:07:40,404
Evidence?

139
00:07:40,943 --> 00:07:41,635
What evidence?

140
00:07:42,289 --> 00:07:43,404
It's all hearsay.

141
00:07:43,712 --> 00:07:44,635
There's no evidence.

142
00:07:44,789 --> 00:07:45,943
Just disperse it.

143
00:07:46,750 --> 00:07:48,135
Are you afraid that if exposed,

144
00:07:48,140 --> 00:07:49,289
you'll lose control of power?

145
00:07:49,750 --> 00:07:50,212
You

146
00:07:51,712 --> 00:07:53,135
are talking nonsense.

147
00:07:53,366 --> 00:07:54,481
Nonsense!

148
00:07:55,135 --> 00:07:55,866
Step aside!

149
00:07:56,366 --> 00:07:56,866
Step aside!

150
00:07:56,866 --> 00:07:57,827
Explain yourself.

151
00:07:57,827 --> 00:08:01,250
Mr. Saul.

152
00:08:01,250 --> 00:08:01,789
Step aside.

153
00:08:01,943 --> 00:08:02,866
Explain yourself.

154
00:08:03,481 --> 00:08:04,520
Mr. Saul.

155
00:08:10,789 --> 00:08:11,635
Saul.

156
00:08:14,904 --> 00:08:16,135
Do you know your crime?

157
00:08:18,597 --> 00:08:19,481
Your Majesty.

158
00:08:20,673 --> 00:08:22,520
I am innocent.

159
00:08:24,173 --> 00:08:26,827
I have devoted myself to Manbo.

160
00:08:27,212 --> 00:08:28,789
What crime have I committed?

161
00:08:30,523 --> 00:08:31,562
Your Majesty.

162
00:08:32,100 --> 00:08:33,254
Moreover,

163
00:08:35,254 --> 00:08:38,716
Saul is the true mastermind
behind the late queen's death.

164
00:08:42,408 --> 00:08:43,254
Saul.

165
00:08:44,985 --> 00:08:45,870
Explain to me

166
00:08:47,062 --> 00:08:48,370
clearly.

167
00:08:49,831 --> 00:08:50,831
Your Majesty.

168
00:08:51,177 --> 00:08:53,408
This is defamation, all rumors.

169
00:08:53,408 --> 00:08:54,793
Pure nonsense.

170
00:08:55,562 --> 00:08:56,716
Is that so?

171
00:09:03,177 --> 00:09:04,485
Greetings, Your Majesty.

172
00:09:09,639 --> 00:09:11,023
Stand and speak.

173
00:09:14,485 --> 00:09:17,216
The late queen
had a heart attack years ago.

174
00:09:18,023 --> 00:09:20,639
Though I resented her for outranking me,

175
00:09:21,562 --> 00:09:23,331
I didn't have the courage to kill her.

176
00:09:24,370 --> 00:09:25,254
That day,

177
00:09:26,139 --> 00:09:28,023
it was Mr. Saul who stopped me.

178
00:09:29,447 --> 00:09:31,523
And he took the late queen's medicine.

179
00:09:32,331 --> 00:09:36,793
That's why the late queen
couldn't be treated in time.

180
00:09:40,639 --> 00:09:41,716
You confessed.

181
00:09:44,062 --> 00:09:45,370
You fool.

182
00:09:45,908 --> 00:09:47,062
You won't survive either.

183
00:09:49,062 --> 00:09:50,754
But I refuse to live

184
00:09:51,062 --> 00:09:53,754
under the misunderstanding
and hatred of my own son.

185
00:09:57,128 --> 00:09:57,974
Saul.

186
00:09:58,782 --> 00:10:00,667
How dare you

187
00:10:01,320 --> 00:10:03,359
commit such a heinous crime?

188
00:10:04,474 --> 00:10:05,974
A heinous crime?

189
00:10:09,667 --> 00:10:11,897
Your Majesty.

190
00:10:12,436 --> 00:10:14,705
I fought for the honor of the nation.

191
00:10:15,820 --> 00:10:17,128
Stop making excuses.

192
00:10:17,963 --> 00:10:19,925
You acted out of selfish desire.

193
00:10:20,887 --> 00:10:22,694
Have you ever considered the people?

194
00:10:23,848 --> 00:10:26,117
You only think
about controlling everything.

195
00:10:27,656 --> 00:10:30,810
Guards! Take him away!

196
00:10:36,771 --> 00:10:37,771
Step aside!

197
00:10:43,194 --> 00:10:44,733
I am a minister of the state.

198
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:46,771
Your Majesty.

199
00:10:47,925 --> 00:10:51,040
I've served for decades.

200
00:10:52,271 --> 00:10:55,887
I have been loyal to you
and to this nation.

201
00:10:56,271 --> 00:10:58,271
Faithfully and wholeheartedly.

202
00:10:58,540 --> 00:11:01,694
Your Majesty,
I fight for the honor of the nation.

203
00:11:01,694 --> 00:11:03,733
- Take him away!
- Fighting for ideals.

204
00:11:03,733 --> 00:11:05,194
Your Majesty, I fight

205
00:11:05,194 --> 00:11:06,925
for the country.

206
00:11:06,925 --> 00:11:09,771
I am loyal to you, Your Majesty.

207
00:11:09,860 --> 00:11:10,900
Your Majesty!

208
00:11:11,733 --> 00:11:14,540
I am loyal to you, Your Majesty!

209
00:11:14,925 --> 00:11:16,194
Your Majesty!

210
00:11:18,617 --> 00:11:19,156
Your Majesty.

211
00:11:19,963 --> 00:11:21,733
I know my sins are grave.

212
00:11:21,963 --> 00:11:23,540
I do not dare ask for your forgiveness.

213
00:11:24,194 --> 00:11:25,310
I only hope

214
00:11:25,502 --> 00:11:27,540
that you will not take it out on Lin Ge.

215
00:11:28,310 --> 00:11:30,887
He is still an innocent good boy.

216
00:11:32,002 --> 00:11:32,925
Mother.

217
00:11:35,463 --> 00:11:36,348
Lin Ge.

218
00:11:36,848 --> 00:11:38,540
I am sorry to you.

219
00:11:39,771 --> 00:11:40,887
But you must believe,

220
00:11:41,194 --> 00:11:42,233
from the very beginning,

221
00:11:42,848 --> 00:11:45,540
I only wanted to plan a good future
for you.

222
00:11:46,771 --> 00:11:48,194
You are

223
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:50,656
the person I care about most
in this world.

224
00:11:52,002 --> 00:11:52,963
Good son.

225
00:11:54,079 --> 00:11:59,425
From now on, I cannot walk
with you anymore.

226
00:12:04,117 --> 00:12:06,502
Mother, I'm sorry.

227
00:12:06,502 --> 00:12:08,156
I cannot bear to leave you.

228
00:12:08,156 --> 00:12:08,810
Mother.

229
00:12:09,502 --> 00:12:10,617
I'm sorry.

230
00:12:12,694 --> 00:12:14,079
I'm sorry.

231
00:12:23,102 --> 00:12:23,525
Nana.

232
00:12:26,679 --> 00:12:27,563
Where are you going?

233
00:12:31,487 --> 00:12:32,179
Lin Ge.

234
00:12:33,756 --> 00:12:36,217
My father committed such a mistake.

235
00:12:36,833 --> 00:12:38,179
As his daughter,

236
00:12:39,217 --> 00:12:40,525
I cannot escape the blame.

237
00:12:42,063 --> 00:12:44,333
Nana, listen to me carefully.

238
00:12:46,910 --> 00:12:47,871
When I learned

239
00:12:48,448 --> 00:12:49,217
that my mother

240
00:12:49,900 --> 00:12:52,160
was an accomplice
in killing my eldest brother's mother,

241
00:12:52,833 --> 00:12:53,948
I felt the same pain as you.

242
00:12:54,371 --> 00:12:55,794
But my eldest brother taught me

243
00:12:56,794 --> 00:12:57,948
that I don't have

244
00:12:57,948 --> 00:12:59,217
to carry someone else's mistakes.

245
00:12:59,756 --> 00:13:00,410
So,

246
00:13:02,294 --> 00:13:04,063
we don't need to be bound by the past.

247
00:13:05,871 --> 00:13:06,525
Lin Ge,

248
00:13:07,333 --> 00:13:08,602
you are too naive.

249
00:13:09,871 --> 00:13:12,256
Now your mother is imprisoned,

250
00:13:12,640 --> 00:13:14,871
and my father has made such a mistake.

251
00:13:16,602 --> 00:13:17,948
As their children,

252
00:13:18,448 --> 00:13:20,333
if we stay together,

253
00:13:20,679 --> 00:13:21,794
what will the royal family

254
00:13:22,487 --> 00:13:24,256
think of you?

255
00:13:24,256 --> 00:13:25,280
Have you thought about it?

256
00:13:25,563 --> 00:13:26,179
No, I haven't.

257
00:13:27,794 --> 00:13:31,333
I just want to be with you forever.

258
00:13:33,217 --> 00:13:33,871
But

259
00:13:34,948 --> 00:13:36,833
if you stay with me,

260
00:13:37,256 --> 00:13:39,294
you won't be able
to calm the public anger.

261
00:13:39,910 --> 00:13:41,602
So, for you,

262
00:13:43,025 --> 00:13:44,179
I must leave.

263
00:13:46,525 --> 00:13:47,794
You've decided, haven't you?

264
00:13:49,371 --> 00:13:49,948
Yes.

265
00:13:51,448 --> 00:13:54,333
Alright, I respect your choice.

266
00:13:58,794 --> 00:13:59,910
Take care of yourself.

267
00:14:00,525 --> 00:14:01,217
Lin Ge.

268
00:14:04,140 --> 00:14:05,294
Did you forget something?

269
00:14:10,294 --> 00:14:10,756
What?

270
00:14:16,025 --> 00:14:16,794
You forgot me.

271
00:14:18,563 --> 00:14:19,448
Didn't you say

272
00:14:20,371 --> 00:14:21,679
I am your private property?

273
00:14:23,333 --> 00:14:24,448
Then,

274
00:14:25,063 --> 00:14:27,833
where you go, I should go too.

275
00:14:28,063 --> 00:14:31,102
Lin Ge, are you crazy?

276
00:14:31,448 --> 00:14:33,140
Isn't one smart person enough?

277
00:14:34,217 --> 00:14:35,260
Don't follow me anymore.

278
00:14:35,296 --> 00:14:35,912
Nana.

279
00:14:37,220 --> 00:14:38,690
No matter what happens in the future,

280
00:14:39,489 --> 00:14:41,296
no matter where in the world you go,

281
00:14:42,527 --> 00:14:43,604
we will go together.

282
00:14:44,258 --> 00:14:44,796
Alright?

283
00:14:47,373 --> 00:14:47,835
Alright.

284
00:14:48,873 --> 00:14:49,565
Let's go.

285
00:14:53,642 --> 00:14:53,950
Wait.

286
00:14:54,719 --> 00:14:55,681
Isn't that the way back?

287
00:14:55,873 --> 00:14:56,450
Yes.

288
00:14:57,335 --> 00:14:58,104
So,

289
00:14:59,065 --> 00:15:00,412
we should go home.

290
00:15:03,065 --> 00:15:03,565
Let's go.

291
00:15:14,940 --> 00:15:17,420
♪I do this for you♪

292
